3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a1febe1b4fb977f359839d5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJiaona%20Zhang%20has%20previously%20worked%20at%20Airbnb%2C%20Dropbox%2C%20and%20Linktree.%3Cp%3Eskynesher%2FGetty%20Images%3B%20Courtesy%20of%20Jiaona%20Zhang.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgodfather-ai-geoffrey-hinton-cs-degrees-valuable-learn-to-code-2025-12%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EComputer%20science%20degrees%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20no%20longer%20the%20key%20to%20breaking%20into%20tech%2C%20says%20Jiaona%20Zhang.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EZhang%2C%20a%20CPO%20and%20part-time%20Stanford%20lecturer%2C%20thinks%20students%20should%20focus%20on%20building.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPeople%20with%20curiosity%20and%20drive%20are%20likely%20to%20succeed%20in%20the%20age%20of%20AI%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Jiaona%20Zhang%2C%20the%20CPO%20at%20the%20AI%20software%20company%2C%20Laurel.%20She%20previously%20worked%20in%20product%3C%2Fem%3E%20at%20%3Cem%3EAirbnb%2C%20WeWork%2C%20and%20Linktree.%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ESince%202018%2C%20she%20has%20taught%20an%20annual%20graduate-level%20class%20in%20product%20management%20fundamentals%20at%20Stanford%2C%20in-person%20and%20online.%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EShe%20is%20in%20her%20late%2030s%20and%20lives%20in%20the%20San%20Francisco%20Bay%20Area.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%20teaching%20in%202018%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclaude-code-creator-advice-cs-grads-startup-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecomputer%20science%20graduates%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20finding%20great%2C%20well-paid%20jobs%20at%20top%20companies.%20Students%20could%20expect%20to%20earn%20a%20base%20salary%20of%20%24120%2C000%20with%20equity%20on%20top.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20the%20pathway%20of%20studying%20CS%2C%20doing%20a%20giant%20interview%20loop%20when%20big%20companies%20come%20to%20campus%2C%20getting%20in%2C%20and%20working%20your%20way%20up%20the%20company%20seems%20to%20be%20getting%20obliterated.%20I%3Cem%3E'%3C%2Fem%3Eve%20noticed%20those%20entry-level%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-broken-career-ladder-gen-z-entry-level-jobs-ai-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoffers%20drying%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20students%20gravitating%20to%20smaller%20startups%20or%20entrepreneurship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hard%2C%20mundane%20things%20students%20learn%20in%20computer%20science%20and%20the%20tasks%20a%20software%20engineer%20does%20at%20the%20junior%20level%20are%20now%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-ladder-software-engineers-collapsing-ai-google-meta-coding-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edone%20by%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20can%20build%20a%20product%20in%20a%20day%20or%20an%20hour%2C%20even%20if%20you%20aren't%20super%20technical.%20In%20many%20cases%2C%20entrepreneurs%20can%20capture%20so%20much%20value%20at%20an%20unprecedented%20pace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20no%20longer%20just%20about%20whether%20you%20chose%20the%20right%20major%20and%20got%20on%20the%20right%20path.%20Over%20the%20next%2010%20years%2C%20I%20think%20the%20emphasis%20will%20shift%20away%20from%20what%20you've%20studied%20toward%20what%20you're%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudents%20are%20doing%20a%20lot%20of%20soul-searching.%20They're%20asking%20themselves%20what%20problem%20they%20really%20want%20to%20work%20on%2C%20or%20whether%20they%20want%20to%20be%20a%20founder.%20Anyone%20can%20do%20anything%2C%20so%20what%20do%20you%20really%20want%20to%20do%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2242ee40f5-8dfc-4318-a8a1-448f7e2e58a0%5C%22%3EI'm%20looking%20for%20workers%20who%20are%20builders%20with%20curiosity%20and%20drive%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStudents%20don't%20need%20to%20master%20every%20single%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-use-ai-for-investing-options-trader-beat-sp500-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20tool%3C%2Fa%3E%20out%20there.%20Instead%2C%20they%20need%20to%20hone%20their%20skill%20set%20to%20spot%20opportunities.%20One%20of%20the%20reasons%20I%20think%20students%20are%20interested%20in%20my%20Stanford%20product%20course%20is%20because%20I%20teach%20how%20to%20understand%20the%20user%20and%20build%20unique%20insight%20into%20a%20market%20or%20problem.%20If%20you're%20able%20to%20identify%20a%20user%20group%20and%20work%20out%20what%20problem%20they're%20experiencing%2C%20your%20product%20is%20more%20likely%20to%20hit%20the%20bull's-eye.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20interview%20candidates%20at%20Laurel%2C%20I%20have%20them%20share%20their%20screen%20and%20walk%20me%20through%20how%20they%20use%20AI%2C%20and%20ask%20what%20they're%20building%20and%20when%20they%20last%20replaced%20tedious%20manual%20work%20with%20AI.%20A%20candidate's%20level%20of%20agency%20is%20highly%20related%20to%20how%20good%20an%20employee%20I%20think%20they%20will%20be.%20Technology%20has%20leaped%20forward%2C%20and%20it's%20really%20going%20to%20benefit%20those%20who%20are%20curious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20about%20being%20technical%2C%20but%20about%20being%20a%20builder%2C%20meaning%20you%20have%20curiosity%20and%20drive%2C%20and%20do%20the%20thing%20without%20waiting%20to%20be%20told.%20Those%20are%20the%20ingredients%20of%20success%20for%20the%20next%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20breaking%20into%20tech%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Accheong%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eccheong%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20t