ina%2C%20felt%20the%20impact%20of%20this%20shift%20in%20January%20when%20she%20booted%20up%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-startups-claude-has-already-won-the-ai-coding-wars-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAnthropic's%20Claude%20Code%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20build%20a%20payment%20feature%20for%20one%20of%20her%20company's%20clients.%20Coding%20such%20a%20sophisticated%20project%20by%20hand%20would%20have%20taken%20two%20or%20three%20days%2C%20she%20said.%20Claude%20did%20it%20in%20just%20over%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20felt%20like%20the%20point%20of%20no%20return%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThis%20industry%20is%20not%20going%20to%20be%20the%20same.%20My%20job%20is%20not%20going%20to%20be%20the%20same.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Great%20Coding%20Reset%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20multi-part%20series%20exploring%20how%20AI%20has%20sparked%20an%20existential%20transformation%20in%20software%20engineering.%20Next%20week%2C%20we%20look%20at%20how%20AI%20coding%20has%20turbocharged%20some%20engineers%20and%20what%20it%20would%20take%20to%20unlock%20a%20wider%20productivity%20boom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fthe-great-coding-reset%3Ffollow%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFollow%20here%20to%20receive%20an%20alert%20about%20the%20next%20piece%20in%20the%20series.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAndrej%20Karpathy%2C%20a%20former%20founding%20research%20scientist%20at%20OpenAI%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-hires-andrej-karpathy-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecently%20joined%20Anthropic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20February%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fkarpathy%2Fstatus%2F2026731645169185220%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bhard%20to%20communicate%20how%20much%20programming%20has%20changed%20due%20to%20AI%20in%20the%20last%202%20months.%26quot%3B%20Before%20December%2C%20he%20said%2C%20coding%20agents%20%26quot%3Bbasically%20didn't%20work.%26quot%3B%20Suddenly%2C%20there%20was%20takeoff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlash%20forward%20to%20June%2C%20and%20software%20engineering%2C%20a%20role%20that%20employs%20tens%20of%20millions%20globally%2C%20is%20undergoing%20a%20full-blown%20reckoning.%20AI%20is%20sparking%20layoff%20fears%2C%20spawning%20a%20new%20lexicon%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartups-tokenmaxxing-token-quotas-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eterms%20like%20%26quot%3Btokenmaxxing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20driving%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20of%20AI%20investments.%20At%20tech%20giants%20like%20Google%2C%20AI%20is%20now%20writing%20as%20much%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-generated-code-75-gemini-agents-software-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E75%25%20of%20the%20company's%20code%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amy%20Surrett%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a188822b4fb977f35980ded%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221997%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmy%20Surrett%20said%20she's%20seen%20a%20massive%20improvement%20in%20AI%20coding%20tools%20over%20the%20past%20year.%3Cp%3EJesse%20Barber%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20they%20like%20it%20or%20not%2C%20software%20engineers%20are%20patient%20zero%20in%20a%20grand%20workplace%20experiment.%20Coding%2C%20with%20its%20clearly%20defined%20rules%2C%20has%20been%20more%20prone%20to%20AI%20disruption%20than%20other%20professions%2C%20and%20the%20lessons%20engineers%20are%20learning%20could%20be%20broadly%20relevant%20as%20the%20technology%20begins%20to%20disrupt%20other%20white-collar%20work%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20next%20few%20weeks%2C%20Business%20Insider%20will%20explore%20how%20this%20shift%20is%20fundamentally%20reshaping%20the%20software%20industry%20%E2%80%94%20from%20its%20emotional%20impact%20on%20workers%20to%20attempts%20to%20unlock%20AI's%20productivity%20potential%20%E2%80%94%20as%20part%20of%20a%20series%20we're%20calling%20%26quot%3BThe%20Great%20Coding%20Reset.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20what%20does%20it%20mean%20to%20be%20a%20coder%20if%20you%20can%20build%20an%20app%20without%20coding%3F%20If%20software%20engineers%20don't%20need%20to%20write%20code%20directly%2C%20what%20new%20opportunities%20arise%3F%20And%2C%20perhaps%20most%20existentially%2C%20will%20the%20very%20developers%20who%20make%20and%20improve%20these%20AI%20tools%20automate%20themselves%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20us%20%E2%80%94%20out%20of%20jobs%20altogether%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b9ebd6fb-a364-4826-a163-4f377c44fffc%5C%22%3EEverything%20collides%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESoftware%20engineering%20has%20always%20been%20an%20industry%20of%20reinvention%2C%20long%20before%20the%20release%20of%20Anthropic's%20Opus%204.5%20and%20OpenAI's%205.2%E2%80%91Codex%20model%20this%20past%20winter.%20The%20dawn%20of%20personal%20computers%20in%20the%201970s%20created%20a%20gold%20rush%20for%20talent%20who%20could%20build%20operating%20systems%20and%20design%20programming%20languages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20who%20designed%20systems%20for%20the%20desktop%20era%20scrambled%20when%20the%20internet%20rewrote%20the%20rules%2C%20then%20again%20when%20mobile%20did%20the%20same.%20Now%2C%20thanks%20to%20platforms%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmake-app-cursor-lovable-base44-vibe-coding-tools-comparison-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELovable%20and%20Base44%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20don't%20even%20need%20to%20code%20to%20build%20a%20functioning%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20engineers%2C%20the%20pace%20of%20change%20has%20been%20invigorating%20%E2%80%94%20and%20also%20destabilizing.%20In%20February%2C%20popular%20engineering%20newsletter%20Latent%20Space%20launched%20a%20spin-off%20website%20that%20epitomized%20the%20feeling%20many%20technical%20workers%20were%20experiencing.%20Its%20name%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwtfhappened2025.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewtfhappened2025.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKent%20Dodds%20left%20his%20job%20at%20PayPal%20in%202019%20to%20run%20a%20business%20teaching%20software%20engineers.%20He%20wanted%20to%20build%20a%20tool%20that%20would%20let%20his%20students%20download%20his%20videos%20to%20watch%20offline%2C%20while%20also%20encrypting%20them%20to%20prevent%20unauthorized%20sharing.%20In%20January%2C%20he%20set%20up%20an%20agent%20with%20Cursor%2C%20an%20AI-assisted%20coding%20tool%2C%20which%20%26quot%3Bnailed%20it%20on%20first%20try%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Potentially%20weeks%20of%20work%20had%20evaporated%20in%20a%20single%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kent%20Dodds%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a1883cb2ab5f9757add590f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKent%20Dodds%2C%20who%20teaches%20software%20engineers%2C%20said%20he's%20seen%20a%20%26quot%3Bdrastic%20decline%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20number%20of%20questions%20he%20receives%20from%20students.%3Cp%3ENiki%20Chan%20Wylie%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20was%20my%20first%20existential%20crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wouldn't%20be%20his%20last.%20Over%20the%20past%20several%20months%2C%20these%20models%20have%20continued%20to%20improve%2C%20which%20Dodds%20said%20means%20they%20are%20%26quot%3Bbehaving%20a%20lot%20more%20like%20a%20regular%20software%20developer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20what%20the%20ceiling%20is%2C%20or%20how%20fast%20we're%20going%20to%20hit%20it%2C%20but%20we%20certainly%20aren't%20anywhere%20close%20to%20it%20just%20yet%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fca84772-9006-4516-b2ce-55212cd60913%5C%22%3E'Agents%20take%20over%20the%20world'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20AI%20Engineer%20Europe%20conference%20in%20London%20in%20April%2C%20the%20room%20buzzed%20with%20excitement%20as%20engineers%20tried%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20the%20shift%20happening%20under%20their%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20last%20six%20months%2C%20we%20have%20seen%20coding%20agents%20take%20over%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Ryan%20Lopopolo%2C%20a%20member%20of%20OpenAI's%20technical%20staff%2C%20said%20onstage.%20As%20he%20described%20it%2C%20the%20role%20of%20the%20software%20engineer%20was%20quickly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-agent-management-software-engineer-openai-anthropic-google-coding-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecoming%20that%20of%20an%20agent%20supervisor%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverseeing%20agents%20used%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bmore%20of%20a%20synchronous%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20Alex%20Ponomarev%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Volt%2C%20a%20boutique%20software%20development%20agency%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BYou'd%20have%20Claude%20Code%20running%2C%20it%20does%20something%2C%20then%20it%20stops%2C%20you%20have%20to%20tell%20it%20what%20to%20do%20next.%26quot%3B%20That's%20no%20longer%20the%20case%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20always%20mean%20less%20work.%20Some%20engineers%20have%20expressed%20frustration%20about%20having%20to%20clean%20up%20AI-generated%20code%20or%20fix%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdevelopers-warn-flood-vibe-coded-apps-could-slow-apple-approvals-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclunky%20vibe-coded%20apps%3C%2Fa%3E%20built%20by%20tech-novice%20coworkers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20more%20time%20spent%20managing%20agents%20and%20less%20time%20%3Cem%3Ein%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20code%2C%20some%20developers'%20schedules%20look%20different%2C%20as%20they%20restructure%20tasks%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-creating-identity-crisis-for-software-engineers-coders-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecreating%20specs%20for%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cu%3E%20%3C%2Fu%3Eand%20take%20breaks%20while%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-usage-limits-causing-some-to-restructure-their-workday-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etoken%20limits%20reset.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20basically%20not%20even%20worth%20my%20time%20to%20be%20manually%20writing%20code%20when%20I%20can%20have%20something%20like%20Claude%20doing%20it%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Danial%20Qureshi%2C%20a%20software%20developer%20in%20Toronto%2C%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2205e515c0-ac3a-4e16-8097-07ca41b6856e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20to%20build%20%E2%80%94%20not%20how%20to%20build%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20catch%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20that%20this%20extraordinary%20new%20power%20is%20nobody's%20secret%20weapon.%20If%20you%20have%20it%2C%20so%20does%20everyone%20else%2C%20and%20it's%20getting%20harder%20to%20compete%20against%20the%20bots.%20In%20response%2C%20engineers%20are%20doubling%20down%20on%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-coding-changing-software-developer-role-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edistinctly%20human%20qualities%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kent%20Dodds%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a18894eb4fb977f35980e07%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20teaching%20the%20last%20skill%20that%20the%20last%20software%20engineer%20needs%20to%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dodds.%3Cp%3ENiki%20Chan%20Wylie%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20year%2C%20Dodds%20said%20the%20number%20of%20questions%20he%20receives%20from%20students%20has%20seen%20a%20%26quot%3Bdrastic%20decline.%26quot%3B%20He%20chalks%20it%20up%20to%20coding%20agents'%20ability%20to%20answer%20those%20queries%20much%20faster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhere%20Dodds%20not%20long%20ago%20would%20teach%20engineers%20how%20to%20code%2C%20today%20he%20has%20a%20new%20curriculum%20for%20what%20he%20calls%20%26quot%3Bproduct%20engineering%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20focus%20on%20%3Cem%3Ewhat%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20build%2C%20not%20%3Cem%3Ehow%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20build%20it.%20The%20value%20of%20humans%2C%20as%20Dodds%20sees%20it%2C%20is%20judgment.%20What%20problems%20should%20be%20solved%3F%20What%20are%20the%20benefits%20and%20drawbacks%3F%20What%20would%20be%20truly%20useful%20to%20the%20user%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20teaching%20the%20last%20skill%20that%20the%20last%20software%20engineer%20needs%20to%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20Surrett%20is%20reckoning%20with%20how%20her%20job%20has%20changed.%20She%20graduated%20with%20a%20Bachelor's%20in%20software%20development%20in%202022%2C%20just%20a%20few%20months%20before%20ChatGPT%20launched.%20AI%20has%20fundamentally%20changed%20the%20way%20she%20expects%20to%20use%20her%20education.%20She%20estimated%20that%20AI%20tools%20were%20writing%205-10%25%20of%20her%20code%20a%20year%20ago%20and%20said%20it's%20now%20around%2080-90%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amy%20Surrett%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a1885cbb4fb977f35980db8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221997%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESurrett%20estimated%20that%20AI%20tools%20were%20writing%205-10%25%20of%20her%20code%20a%20year%20ago.%20It's%20now%20around%2080-90%25%2C%20she%20said.%3Cp%3EJesse%20Barber%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20double-edged%20sword%2C%20because%20in%20some%20ways%20I'm%20getting%20more%20done%20but%20also%20doing%20less%20work%2C%20so%20it%20feels%20less%20productive%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Surrett.%20While%20she%20worries%20about%20the%20implications%20on%20an%20industry%20she%20is%20still%20fresh%20to%2C%20she%20still%20thinks%20she%20has%20an%20edge.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20patterns%20of%20writing%20good%20software%20that%20someone%20who%20downloaded%20Claude%20Code%20last%20week%20won't%20know.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20she's%20sharpening%20other%20skills.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20leaning%20on%20some%20of%20the%20soft%20skills%20AI%20can't%20really%20replace%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Surrett.%20%26quot%3BFiguring%20out%20how%20to%20phrase%20things%2C%20what%20a%20client%20wants%2C%20having%20that%20creativity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20it's%20impossible%20to%20ignore%20the%20forces%20reshaping%20tech%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flist-companies-replacing-human-employees-with-ai-layoffs-workforce-reductions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompanies%20cite%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20rounds%20of%20sweeping%20layoffs%20while%20doubling%20down%20on%20massive%20AI%20investments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20recently%2C%20software%20developers%20have%20been%20relatively%20shielded%20from%20layoff%20fears.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblock-software-engineer-layoff-jack-dorsey-job-search-ai-shift-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThat%20perception%20has%20changed%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20recently%20there%20has%20been%20a%20modest%20uptick%20in%20software%20engineering%20job%20postings%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20job%20site%20Indeed.%20With%20AI%20producing%20more%20code%20than%20ever%2C%20more%20humans%20could%20be%20needed%20to%20oversee%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FhLLbn%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Line%20chart%20of%20software%20development%20job%20postings%20on%20Indeed%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FhLLbn%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20person%20who%20isn't%20worried%20about%20AI%20is%20Jason%20Young%2C%20an%20engineer%20of%2030%20years.%20He's%20leaning%20into%20what%20sets%20him%20apart%20from%20the%20bots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20couple%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20felt%20very%20threatened%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Young%2C%20now%20a%20lead%20engineer%20at%20smart%20kiosk%20maker%20ChargeItSpot%2C%20of%20the%20agents%20he's%20been%20experimenting%20with.%20Yet%20the%20more%20time%20he's%20spent%20with%20them%2C%20the%20more%20confident%20he's%20become%20that%20human%20judgment%20will%20remain%20crucial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Young%2C%20the%20essence%20of%20engineering%20is%20in%20understanding%20the%20problem%2C%20not%20mass-producing%20lines%20of%20code.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20writing%20of%20text%20%E2%80%94%20that%20isn't%20what%20being%20a%20software%20engineer%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Young.%20%26quot%3BAnyone%20who%20thinks%20otherwise%20has%20a%20wild%20misunderstanding%20of%20software%20engineering.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d91c600a-7de3-4d47-8e90-fbdf58ad8821%5C%22%3EWhat%20do%20you%20think%20about%20how%20the%20software%20engineering%20industry%20is%20changing%3F%20Let%20us%20know%20below%3A%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%2F%2Fembed.typeform.com%2Fnext%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20data-tf-live%3D%5C%2201KT4V1KSD7NAQBY7K1VBHHSCT%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-coding-agents-tools-software-engineering-jobs-future-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780479961000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a1f0ae1b4fb977f359835bb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-coding-agents-tools-software-engineering-jobs-future-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20space%20of%20a%20few%20weeks%2C%20OpenAI%2C%20Anthropic%2C%20and%20Google%20released%20new%20AI%20models.%20Now%2C%20coders%20are%20rethinking%20their%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20and%20what%20comes%20next.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hlangley%40businessinsider.com%20(Hugh%20Langley)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pacsun's%20CEO%20said%20she%20cut%20meetings%20by%2060%25%2C%20but%20some%20of%20the%20best%20discussions%20have%20been%204%20hours%20long%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222666%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Brieane%20Olson%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a10614c51ede568c7e175d2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBrieane%20Olson%20cut%20down%20the%20company's%20meetings%20by%2060%25%20since%20becoming%20CEO%20at%20Pacsun.%3Cp%3ESlaven%20Vlasic%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20Delivering%20Good%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBrieane%20Olson%20says%20she's%20worked%20to%20reduce%20meetings%20by%2060%25%20since%20becoming%20CEO%20at%20Pacsun.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHowever%2C%20she%20says%20an%20over-focus%20on%20efficiency%20can%20get%20in%20the%20way%20of%20innovation%20and%20brainstorming.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhile%20rare%2C%20Olson%20says%20some%20of%20the%20best%20conversations%20at%20Pacsun%20have%20gone%20on%20for%20four%20hours.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMeetings%20are%20often%20treated%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsnowflake-ceo-shares-rules-for-meetings-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eultimate%20representation%20of%20corporate%20bureaucracy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20leading%20some%20execs%20to%20try%20to%20eliminate%20them%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Pacsun%20CEO%20Brieane%20Olson%20stepped%20up%20to%20lead%20the%20clothing%20brand%20three%20years%20ago%2C%20she%20said%20she%20worked%20to%20reduce%20the%20company's%20overall%20meeting%20load%20by%20roughly%2060%25.%20The%20move%20was%20part%20of%20an%20effort%20to%20open%20up%20more%20space%20for%20focus%2C%20creativity%2C%20and%20execution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOlson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20she%20tries%20to%20make%20sure%20meetings%20are%20purposeful%20and%20productive%20for%20everyone%20in%20the%20room.%20She%20added%20that%20not%20every%20conversation%20needs%20to%20be%20a%20meeting%20and%20that%20part%20of%20leading%20the%20company%20means%20knowing%20when%20smaller%20discussions%2C%20quick%20decisions%2C%20and%20written%20communication%20can%20be%20more%20efficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20here%20in%20service%20to%20my%20team.%20So%2C%20the%20meetings%20have%20to%20be%20useful%20to%20them%20and%20I%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20I'm%20present%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Cstrong%3Es%3C%2Fstrong%3Eaid%20Olson%2C%20who%20recently%20published%20the%20leadership%20book%20%26quot%3BCo-Created%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20brand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c07855df-8f98-409b-b5f2-e21833188db3%5C%22%3EA%20balance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOlson%20said%20that%20while%20meetings%20should%20have%20a%20goal%2C%20the%20path%20to%20getting%20there%20is%20not%20always%20linear%2C%20especially%20when%20teams%20are%20working%20through%20strategy%2C%20innovation%2C%20or%20long-term%20planning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20important%20to%20be%20clear%20on%20the%20topic%20and%20the%20outcome%2C%26quot%3B%20Olson%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20how%20you%20get%20there%20might%20not%20be%20as%20direct%20as%20you%20think.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20she's%20cut%20down%20the%20number%20of%20meetings%20overall%2C%20she%20said%20she%20believes%20certain%20conversations%20can%20still%20benefit%20from%20live%20discussion%2C%20especially%20when%20teams%20are%20solving%20problems%2C%20brainstorming%20ideas%2C%20or%20debating%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOlson%20said%20that%20over-focusing%20on%20efficiency%20can%20limit%20%26quot%3Btrue%20innovation%2C%20creativity%2C%20curiosity%2C%20and%20brainstorming.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20of%20our%20best%20conversations%20as%20a%20leadership%20team%20have%20been%20when%20the%20meeting%20went%20four%20hours%20because%20people%20are%20actually%20speaking%20in%20the%20room%2C%26quot%3B%20Olson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20conversations%20aren't%20the%20norm%20at%20Pacsun%2C%20however.%20Olson%20said%20those%20meetings%20have%20taken%20place%20during%20the%20retailer's%20long-range%20planning%20sessions%2C%20which%20occur%20twice%20a%20year%20over%20a%20two%20or%20three-day%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOlson%20said%20she's%20trying%20to%20build%20a%20culture%20where%20all%20voices%20are%20heard.%20To%20do%20that%2C%20you%20need%20to%20%26quot%3Bcreate%20a%20little%20more%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20She%20added%20that%20listening%20is%20especially%20important%20for%20a%20company%20that%20prides%20itself%20on%20community%20and%20creativity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOlson%20isn't%20alone%20in%20articulating%20her%20approach%20to%20meetings.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Instagram%20chief%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram-adam-mosseri-getting-rid-of-workers-dread-meetings-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAdam%20Mosseri%20released%20a%20memo%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20said%20recurring%20meetings%20would%20be%20canceled%20every%20six%20months%20and%20only%20re-added%20if%20%26quot%3Babsolutely%20necessary.%26quot%3B%20The%20executive%20also%20encouraged%20making%20recurring%20one-on-ones%20biweekly%20%26quot%3Bby%20default%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20workers%20should%20decline%20meetings%20that%20interfere%20with%20%26quot%3Bfocus%20blocks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJeff%20Bezos%20also%20has%20his%20own%20unique%20meeting%20style.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-messy-meetings-amazon-founder-achieve-more-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EThe%20billionaire%20has%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20meetings%20he%20finds%20most%20useful%20start%20with%20six-page%20memos%2C%20followed%20by%2030%20minutes%20of%20reading%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bmessy%26quot%3B%20discussion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpacsun-ceo-brieane-olson-shares-meeting-philosophy-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780479781000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a10613051ede568c7e175d0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpacsun-ceo-brieane-olson-shares-meeting-philosophy-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20move%20is%20part%20of%20an%20effort%20to%20create%20more%20space%20for%20focus%2C%20creativity%2C%20and%20execution%2C%20CEO%20Brieane%20Olson%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aaltchek%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Altchek)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Things%20aren't%20going%20too%20well%2C'%20shares%20Jojo%20Siwa%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780479694000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-131481071%2Cimgsize-41396.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fweb-series%2Fnews%2Fenglish%2Fjojo-siwa-reveals-gnarly-eye-infection-and-terrible-concussion-things-arent-going-too-well%2Farticleshow%2F131481078.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesof